5. Use the `off` method to unbind event handlers: If you have bound event handlers using the `on` method, be sure to use the `off` method to unbind them when they are no longer needed.

ps aux | grep myprocess

```
tcpdump -i interface -p pid
```

```
tcpdump -i eth0 -p 12345
```
This command will capture all TCP traffic to and from the specified process and display it in real-time on the terminal. The CV joint consists of an inner and outer joint, which are connected by an axle shaft. The inner joint is connected to the transmission, while the outer joint is connected to the wheel hub. The joint is covered with a rubber or plastic boot to protect it from dirt and debris and to keep the grease inside.

As the wheels move up and down over bumps, the suspension travels through its range of motion, causing the angle of the CV joint to change. The CV joint is designed to accommodate for these changes in angle, allowing for smooth and consistent power transfer to the wheels.

Some of the benefits of SD-WAN include improved network performance, increased reliability, lower costs, and greater agility in deploying and managing network services. It is often used by organizations with multiple locations, remote workers, and cloud-based applications.

context.content: write a play where tamil and sanskrit argue themselves on superiority

Scene: A public square in ancient India. Tamil and Sanskrit are standing on opposite sides, each representing their own language.

(Tamil steps forward)

Tamil: Greetings, Sanskrit! It is I, Tamil, the language of the common people.

Sanskrit: (with a condescending tone) Greetings, Tamil. How quaint to see you here representing your...limited language.

Tamil: Limited? I beg to differ. My language has been spoken by the people of the South for thousands of years and has a rich culture and history.

Sanskrit: (sighs) Yes, but it is nothing compared to the beauty and sophistication of Sanskrit, the language of the gods.

Tamil: Beauty and sophistication? Those are subjective qualities. What is important is that Tamil is the language of the people and is used in their daily lives.

Sanskrit: (laughs) How quaint. The people may use Tamil, but it is Sanskrit that is used in literature, science, and religion.

Tamil: That may be true, but my language has been adapted to the needs of the people, whereas Sanskrit is a dead language, only studied by the elite.

Sanskrit: (outraged) Dead? How dare you! Sanskrit is the root of all Indo-European languages, including your own.

Tamil: (smiling) That may be so, but it is Tamil that has evolved and adapted, spreading its influence far beyond the borders of India.

Sanskrit: (defeated) I suppose you have a point. But still, the beauty and sophistication of Sanskrit cannot be matched.

Tamil: (smiling) Beauty is in the eye of the beholder, my friend. Each language has its own unique qualities and strengths, and both Tamil and Sanskrit have a place in the world.

(Both step back and bow to each other)

End of Scene.
